                                         JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested a newly married woman on murder charges after she allegedly poisoned her husband's milk and it inadvertently killed 17 other people in a remote village. The Associated Press is reporting the incident took place last week and officers have so far arrested the 21-year-old bride - who was married against her will - and her lover in connection with this murder case.